  cat <<EOF
Usage:
  equitystack current-admin <command> [args]

Commands:
  discover   Wrapper for scripts/discover_current_admin_updates.py
  gen-batch  Wrapper for scripts/generate_current_admin_batch_from_discovery.py
  export     Wrapper for scripts/export_current_admin_discovery_candidates.py
  normalize  Wrapper for scripts/normalize_current_admin_batch.py
  ai-review  Wrapper for scripts/review_current_admin_batch_with_openai_batch.py
  queue      Wrapper for scripts/apply_current_admin_ai_review.py
  promote-review
             Promote an enriched review artifact into the canonical queue
  run        Discover and generate the next batch by default, then normalize, review, and queue it
  review     Generate or finalize operator decisions for a review artifact
  apply      Run pre-commit, import dry-run, optional apply, and validation
  status     Show current-admin batch state and recommended next step
  workflow   Guided artifact-first operator workflow helpers
  pre-commit Wrapper for scripts/build_current_admin_precommit_review.py
  import     Wrapper for scripts/import_curated_current_admin_batch.py
  validate   Wrapper for scripts/validate_current_admin_import.py

Defaults:
  current-admin ai-review, current-admin run, and workflow decision steps default to:
    openai-model   $DEFAULT_CURRENT_ADMIN_REVIEW_MODEL
    verifier-model $DEFAULT_CURRENT_ADMIN_VERIFIER_MODEL
    fallback-model $DEFAULT_CURRENT_ADMIN_FALLBACK_MODEL
    openai-base-url $DEFAULT_CURRENT_ADMIN_OPENAI_BASE_URL

  current-admin discovery defaults to:
    model       $DEFAULT_MODEL_VERIFIER
    timeout     ${DEFAULT_OLLAMA_TIMEOUT_VERIFIER}s
    llm endpoint $DEFAULT_OLLAMA_URL

Path handling:
  Current-admin path flags accept python-rooted paths like data/... or reports/... .
  The installed ~/bin/equitystack wrapper also accepts repo-rooted paths like
  python/data/... or python/reports/... and normalizes them automatically.

OpenAI Batch lifecycle:
  Use current-admin ai-review --input <normalized-or-ai-review.json> with:
    --batch-status   show local metadata plus remote status when available
    --batch-poll     poll an existing batch without resubmitting
    --batch-fetch    fetch output/error files without resubmitting
    --batch-inspect  show local readiness and validation counts
    --batch-resume   poll, fetch, and rebuild the canonical review artifact when ready
